`clamp` can be implemented directly from the contract:

```ts
export function clamp(value: number, minimum: number, maximum: number): number {
  if (value < minimum) {
    return minimum;
  }

  if (value > maximum) {
    return maximum;
  }

  return value;
}
```

Three representative tests:

```ts
import { strict as assert } from "node:assert";

assert.equal(clamp(-5, 0, 10), 0);   // below range -> minimum
assert.equal(clamp(15, 0, 10), 10);  // above range -> maximum
assert.equal(clamp(7, 0, 10), 7);    // inside range -> unchanged
```

Review: this matches the full stated contract exactly. With finite inputs and `minimum <= maximum`, there are no additional edge conditions to handle.
